Are you ready for the next big challenge in your career? At TechnologyOne, we
are redefining the future of the ERP software that our customers use to run
their organisations and ultimately deliver outcomes for the communities we
live within, and we need your help! We are looking for an experienced Software
Architect to help design, and lead development teams to build, our next
generation, Student Digital Experience application - Student DXP.  
  
As an experienced Architect, capable of innovative architectural vision and
delivery. You'll take responsibility for components of our Student Digital
Experience software solution and work closely with the Product Owner to
deliver solutions that wow our customers. You'll work with other members of
our Engineering team to scope, architect and estimate development while
getting your hands dirty writing code. You'll be able to use your .NET, React
and SQL skills to design elegant and cost-effective solutions.  
  
As a leader, you'll guide and mentor a small team of Developers to solve the
complex, transforming business and making life simple - by leveraging their
innovation, drive and determination.  

##  ** What you'll be doing… **

  * Design, Architect and Develop SaaS-based student experience solutions, considering scalability, reliability, performance, deployment strategies, cost-optimisation, compliance and security. 
  * Providing leadership, technical guidance and mentorship to Software Developers and other team members, fostering a culture of innovation and continuous learning 
  * Collaborating with other Architects, Product Owners, and software Developers to understand business requirements and translate them into technical specifications and architecture; then work to realise their delivery 
  * Developing and maintaining a deep understanding of the existing TechnologyOne cloud infrastructure, platforms, and services, and identify opportunities for optimization and enhancement. 
  * Become the expert in your domain by coaching and mentoring peers; adhering to TechnologyOne development methodologies and aligning to the TechnologyOne culture and values and fostering a 'Can Do Culture' 
  * Clearly articulate technical issues to non-technical audiences through technical showcases, sharing information and educating teams 
  * Ensure the security and compliance of the software, implementing robust security controls, monitoring mechanisms, and disaster recovery plans. 

##  ** Your Talents… **

  * At our core we write in C#, React and SQL. Experience with HTML5, MVC & JQuery will be well utilised, although isn't required 
  * Proven experience designing, developing and delivering end to end applications in SaaS native platforms such as AWS, Azure or Google Cloud Platform. 
  * Solid understanding of SaaS-native architecture patterns, microservices, serverless computing, containerization, networking, security and event driven architectures. 
  * Leadership Capability with an ability to build a collective sense of direction fostering a collaborative culture inspiring delivery of high quality standards of work 
  * Exceptional communication capability, with the ability to develop concepts logically and concisely, promoting trust & commitment through consistent open communication 
  * Commercial acumen, able to set goals & plans for areas of responsibility aligned with strategic direction 
  * A thorough understanding and application of non-functional requirements of the software including security and privacy of software 
  * Relevant degree, qualification or job experience within the industry 

##  ** Benefits… **

  * Competitive remuneration package 
  * Industry leading employee share plan 
  * Free gym membership in our onsite Health Lab 
  * Additional 2.5 days of leave per year dedicated to volunteering at a charity of your choice 
  * Free breakfast and coffee on-site 

  
_ TechnologyOne is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer who values
diversity and an inclusive workplace. We aim to recruit a diverse range of
people with a diverse range of talents to help us to deliver on our mission to
better our community. _ _ If you meet a number of the requirements (and not
all), we encourage you to submit your application. _  
  

##  Who we are…

TechnologyOne (ASX: TNE) is Australia's largest enterprise software company
and one of Australia's top 100 ASX-listed companies, with locations across six
countries. We provide a global SaaS ERP solution that transforms business and
makes life simple for our customers. Our deeply integrated enterprise SaaS
solution is available on any device, anywhere and anytime and is incredibly
easy to use. Over 1,200 leading corporations, government agencies, local
councils and universities are powered by our software.  
  
For more than 36 years, we have been providing our customers enterprise
software that evolves and adapts to new and emerging technologies, allowing
them to focus on their business and not technology.

